nodes.text: Coora was a female individual who served as a cadet within the Galactic Empire's 204th Imperial Fighter Wing during the Galactic Civil War. By 5 ABY, she was promoted to the rank of ensign by Colonel Soran Keize, the commanding officer of the unit, and was assigned to the bridge of the fighter wing's flagship, the bulk freighter Yadeez.

That year, the 204th sought to wipe out all life on the planet Fedovoi End as punishment for the resident Yomo Council's decision to disassociate from the Empire. After Keize broadcasted his intentions on the planet, Coora leaned far over her tactical console, which Keize suspected to be the ensign trying to hide her anxiety. When the colonel gave the go-ahead for the attack, the bridge crew began transmitting queries and relaying orders, and the 204th proceeded to shatter areas of Fedovoi End's polar ice caps, opening up gas pockets and slowly poisoning the planet's atmosphere and population.
Coora appeared in the 2021 novel Victory's Price, the final installment of the Star Wars: Alphabet Squadron trilogy which was written by Alexander Freed.
